<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41022a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41022a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41022a"> 22(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> deceased husband&apos;s / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">si</span></span> brother</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Recent statutes, however, now allow a man to marry his deceased wife&apos;s sister or his <mark>deceased brother&apos;s widow</mark>. He cannot however marry his divorced wife&apos;s sister during the lifetime of his former wife or his brother&apos;s divorced wife during the lifetime of his brother. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 18</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
